comment:
Exit code constants. From [the BSD sysexits manpage][manpage]. Not every
constant here is used, even though some of the unused ones may be
appropriate for errors encountered by pub.

[manpage]: http://www.freebsd.org/cgi/man.cgi?query=sysexits

children.comment: The user did not have sufficient permissions.
children.name: NO_PERM

children.comment: The remote system returned something invalid during a protocol exchange.
children.name: PROTOCOL

children.comment: Temporary failure, indicating something that is not really an error.
children.name: TEMP_FAIL

children.comment: An error occurred while doing I/O on some file.
children.name: IO

children.comment: A user-specified output file cannot be created.
children.name: CANT_CREATE

children.comment: Some system file did not exist or was unreadable.
children.name: OS_FILE

children.comment: An operating system error has been detected.
children.name: OS

children.comment: An internal software error has been detected.
children.name: SOFTWARE

children.comment: The host specified did not exist.
children.name: NO_HOST

children.comment: The user specified did not exist.
children.name: NO_USER

children.comment: An input file did not exist or was unreadable.
children.name: NO_INPUT
